modules.description: Provides functions to parse and generate JSON from and to string values, simplifying common input and output tasks. Works with basic string data and JSON-encoded data structures. Useful for quickly embedding JSON processing in scripts without handling low-level streaming details.

Provides parsing and serialization of JSON data, converting between OCaml values and JSON structures like lists, options, and dictionaries, with support for error handling and S-expression conversions. It simplifies JSON manipulation in scripts by offering convenient input/output functions for strings, channels, and buffers, avoiding complex signal code.
